	(192, 98, 'Double Attack', 'When each member of the Einar Imperium attacks, he may attack one additional time.'),
	(193, 98, 'Stealth Flying', 'When counting spaces for the Einar Imperium''s movement, ignore elevations. The Einar Imperium may fly over water without stopping, pass over obstacles such as ruins. When a member of the Einar Imperium starts to fly, if he is engaged he will not take any leaving engagement attacks.'),
	(196, 99, 'Dwarven Strategic Bonding', 'Before taking a turn with The Axegrinders of Burning Forge, you may first take a turn with any Dwarf Hero you control. If you do not take a turn with any Dwarf Hero you control, add 2 to the Axegrinder''s movement number.'),
	(197, 99, 'Fearless Advantage', 'An Axegrinder of Burning Forge rolls an additional die when attacking or defending against large or huge figures.'),
